This repository intentionally excludes scrapers for copyrighted third-party
aggregator databases (e.g. commercial accident-archive sites, such as the
Aviation Safety Network and the Bureau of Aircraft Accidents Archives, that
assert copyright over their compiled record sets). Only official public-record
sources (national safety investigation authorities, government bulk dumps)
and open/CC0 datasets (Wikidata) are covered.

The `sources-go/aircrash` component fetches airport reference data
(name/city/country/coordinates) from the OpenFlights `airports.dat` dataset
(https://github.com/jpatokal/openflights), compiled from OurAirports
(https://ourairports.com/) public-domain data, at runtime rather than
redistributing it in this repository. See `sources-go/aircrash/migrate-regeocode.py`
for the fetch logic and attribution.
